<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-01-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-01-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.192/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">South</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-01-30T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 30,
                                        1924—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>11. Your 11, January 29, 3 p.m. You may inform Panaman Government that
                            this Government is willing to appoint a Commission to negotiate treaty
                            with Panaman Commission and is willing to commence negotiations in
                            Washington at convenience of Panaman Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>